HEADWORD: Gieseckite
<hw>Gie"seck*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after
<person>Karl <etsep>Giesecke</etsep></person>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral occurring in greenish gray six-sided prisms, having a
greasy luster. It is probably a pseudomorph after el⟦ae⟧olite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gif</ent>⟦br⟧
